Thorax yellowish brown, much darker on meso- and metanota. Legs yellow, with dense yellowish setae; extreme apices of tibiae and entire tarsi brown, tarsal claws reddish brown. Wings hyaline, pterostigmatic area narrowly elongated, pale grayish brown. Forewings with numerous indistinct brownish spots along longitudinal veins. Hindwings immaculate. Veins pale yellow, but brownish in distal half, also with brownish sections in dark markings and costal crossveins of forewings. Rs (
Fig. 3
) 5 or 6 -branched; M 2 -branched.

Abdomen dark brown with venter yellowish brown. Ninth tergum ( Figs. 24, 26 ) subquadrate in dorsal view, with anterior and posterior margins truncate. Ninth sternum (
Figs. 25–26
) short, posteriorly bearing a subtriangular membranous lobe. Tenth tergum (
Figs. 24–27
) nearly as long as 2 / 3 of ninth tergum, obliquely directed dorsad and slightly flattened; in lateral view anterior portion strongly inflated ventrad, bearing numerous spinous setae, posterior half gradually narrowed, leaving an acutely pointed tip; in dorsal view posterior half feebly curved inward. Tenth sternum (
Figs. 25–28
) short, nearly as long as ninth tergum, strongly sclerotized with short lateral arms; median plate medially separated into a pair of narrowly spoon-like, distally produced lobes, each of which laterally bears a long and clavate process, obliquely producing dorsad at subdistal portion. Anus (
Figs. 25–27
) slightly sclerotized ventrad, medially with a broad rectangular sclerotized area in ventral view. A pair of short setose lobes presented beneath anus.

Rs (
Fig. 4
) 5 or 6 -branched in forewings but 5 -branched in hindwings.

Eighth sternum (

Figs. 
29–30

) subtrapezoidal in ventral view, posteriorly bearing a triangular membranous lobe. Ninth gonocoxite (

Fig. 
29

) broadly foliate, with obtuse tip. Tenth tergum (
Figs. 29, 31
) short, acutely produced posteriad, with strongly inflated cercus laterally.
